[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bend, to crook"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to draw, to attract, to turn away, to divert","examples":[{"text":"لفت السياسي نديم الجابري اليوم الجمعة الى ان الخلافات واضحة في التحالف الشيعي ابرزها عملية تسجيل التحالفات لخوض الانتخابات المقبلة ، معتبرا انه لا توجد رؤية مشتركة لمكونات التحالف الوطني بشأن القضايا الوطنية والانشقاقات في الكتل السياسية ناتجة عن فشلها الذريع.","english":"The politician nadīm al-jābirī has on Friday drawn [attention] to the patent disagreements in the Shia alliance, most notably the alliances for the campaign for the election of the coming year, judging that there is no common vision about the constituents of the national alliance over the national affairs and the splits in the political blocs arising from their abject failure."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to turn, to twist, to wring"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"turnip (Brassica rapa subsp. rapa)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"similar plants; kale (Brassica oleracea var. acephala)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"similar plants; rape, rutabaga (Brassica napus)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ل ف ت (l f t) in the sense of twisting or wringing out of the ground, \"to pull up or extract\".\nUltimately, from Proto-Semitic *lapt-.\nCompare: Hebrew לֶפֶת (lefet, “turnip”), Classical Syriac ܠܰܦܬܳܐ (laftā, “turnip”), Akkadian 𒇻𒂠𒊬 (LU.UB₂.SAR /⁠laptu, liptu⁠/, “turnip”)."},"ipa":null}